title: If there is not a clear winner tonight, social media platforms will be in a tough position: Verge's
text: Tim Wu, Columbia Law School professor, and Verge editor-in-chief Nilay Patel join 'Power Lunch' to discuss the role social media platforms could play if societal tensions rise if there is a delayed election result and if the stakes are higher for certain social media platforms than others.

title: 7 Top Stocks to Buy for November

title: Facebook makes more money per user than rivals, but it's running out of growth options
text: The major social media giants all reported year-over-year increases for ARPU in the third quarter, but they face different monetization questions.

title: 'Shark Tank' host Robert Herjavec on cybersecurity risks facing the 2020 president election
text: "Shark Tank" host Robert Herjavec is the founder and CEO of The Herjavec Group, a cybersecurity firm. He joins 'Squawk Alley' to discuss if he has concerns of cyber threats this Election Day.

title: Needham analyst Laura Martin on why the next four years looks bright for Big Tech stocks
text: Chris Senyek, Wolfe Research chief investment strategist, and Laura Martin, Needham analyst, join 'Squawk Alley' to discuss how they are viewing the FAANG names on Election Day and post-Election Day.

title: Facebook: The Perpetual Cacophony Of Noise
text: Digital advertising is a secular growth trend that will continue to inexorably march forward over the next decade, and Facebook will be a major beneficiary. Near-term regulatory headwinds persist, and recent commentary from Facebook's management did nothing to decrease the uncertainty.

title: What Big Tech has to gain—and lose—from a Biden presidency
text: A Biden win means friendlier immigration policies and the likely end of trade war. But the tech giants will still be facing bipartisan goals to enforce antitrust and reform social media.
